GE15
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
SUNDAY TO WEDNESDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND
COASTGUARD AGENCY AT 102300 UTC
ON SUNDAY EVENING A LOW LIES CENTRED 992 OVER THE BREST
PENINSULA BRINGING CYCLONIC CONDITIONS TO THE SERN N SEA
AND THE ENGLISH CHANNEL WITH STRG WINDS AFFECTING SEA
AREAS THAMES DOVER AND WIGHT. WEAK HIGH PRESSURE AFFECTS
THE REST OF THE CULLERCOATS AREA BRINGING SETTLED
CONDITIONS. OVERNIGHT SUNDAY INTO MONDAY THE LOW OVER THE
BREST PENINSULA MOVS NE AND BEGINS TO FILL SLWY TO
BECOME CENTRED 998 GERMAN BIGHT BY MONDAY EVENING. STRG
WINDS WILL AFFECT SEA AREAS DOGGER FISHER GERMAN BIGHT
HUMBER THAMES DOVER AND WIGHT. ELSEWHERE WEAK HIGH
PRESSURE PERSISTS WITH SETTLED CONDITIONS CONTINUING.
OVERNIGHT MONDAY AND INTO TUESDAY HIGH PRESSURE BUILDS
ACROSS THE N SEA DISPLACING THE LOW PRESSURE IN THE SERN
N SEA EWARDS TO CLEAR THE CULLERCOATS AREA BY TUESDAY
MORNING. FOR THE REMAINDER OF TUESDAY AND THROUGHOUT
WEDNESDAY HIGH PRESSURE AFFECTS THE WHOLE OF THE
CULLERCOATS AREA MAINTAINING GENERALLY SETTLED
CONDITIONS
